import groovy.json.JsonSlurper import jxl.* import jxl.write.*
def ResponseMessage = messageExchange.response.responseContent //define a JsonSlurper def jsonSlurper = new JsonSlurper().parseText(ResponseMessage)
assert !(jsonSlurper.isEmpty()) assert jsonSlurper.code != null assert jsonSlurper.error != null
assert jsonSlurper.code == "NR-TMS-C-IMG004" assert jsonSlurper.error == "Image dimensions are not valid"

import groovy.json.JsonSlurper import jxl.* import jxl.write.*
def ResponseMessage = messageExchange.response.responseContent //define a JsonSlurper def jsonSlurper = new JsonSlurper().parseText(ResponseMessage)
assert !(jsonSlurper.isEmpty())
assert jsonSlurper.timestamp != null assert jsonSlurper.payload.emailAddress != null assert jsonSlurper.payload.message != null assert jsonSlurper.payload.emailAddress == "CA@pixel.com" assert jsonSlurper.payload.message == "Profile photo updated successfully."
def processedRecords = jsonSlurper.payload.size(); assert processedRecords == 2
